But I know he will guide and support them. That's the MAMBA MENTALITY. That's the BLACK MAMBA we know. I know it's hard to say but MAMBA OUT. We love and miss you MAMBA FOREVER.

Rest easy KOBE BRYANT.
Rest easy BLACK MAMBA
We will miss your MAMBA MENTALITY
We will remember your moves and the lessons you taught us. Thank you for everything, Kobe Bryant.
MAMBA OUT.

snippet.textDisplay: Why does everyone keep saying “I’m glad they mentioned his parents”. His parents and Kobe had a bad relationship. They CHOOSE not to be mentioned. They choose not to speak. They didn’t want to. Accept it. This is a reflection of the life they choose after rejecting his wife, rejecting his marriage and disrespecting their marriage. Death don’t change reality. Kobe’s dad can call for a conference and there isn’t one news media that wouldn’t come to listen or host him. His mother too. They are choosing to stay in the background. I’m SURE she asked for them to be mentioned.  I’m sure she asked for them to speak. Vanessa lost her Husband. Vanessa lost her daughter. She’s not thinking about being petty.  God bless his parents. But perhaps this teaches us all to value one another and stop being petty. She was married to this man for 20 years! They need to get over it. If Kobe was my son I would of been on like 50 shows already bragging about his legacy doing the ugly cry. I would be all over telling the world about his work and charity. Securing his legacy. If I were his mom nothing can keep me clapping back at idiots like Gayle and Oprah for dragging him after his death but avoiding the real serial rapist like Harvey. Man please. Stop hinting it’s Vanessa when his own mom was just trying to sell his high school memorabilia for a bigger house. This woman stayed with him while he cheated— and she had no prenup.  She could of easily walked away with half. When they got married they he no prenup. Another reason why their family was mad. But they never ever stopped being petty and nasty. Black Women ( i am a black woman) are really mad as biased because he’s a black man with a non-black woman. It’s ridiculous. You really think Vanessa BANNED them from speaking and they were treated badly? Yah right. They would speak to the press! You really think that his sisters, his mom, and even his dad wouldn’t hold a press conference?? They made their choices as parents. It’s the parents who are grimy. Regardless—- you just lost your husband. You just lost your daughter— and you can’t put your differences aside to comfort her and be there for her and your grandkids??? Your grandkids just lost their parent?? And their sister?!? Look at them sitting separate. I’m SURE as hell its not Vanessa as she’s barely able to hold it together losing her daughter and her husband in one go. This is the way they always acted. They never came to his game. Not even his retirement game. They never came to his awards or mvps. Never. This is just how they are. They allowed money to be an issue to divide them.

snippet.textDisplay:
Oh Shaq... you are the man!
Respect on top of respect, and that's because, first, he was a son, a brother, an uncle and a cousin, then ALL the things everybody else said. Shaq did hus speech in a way where not even vanessa can be made. So tasteful and mature!

Another thing that pissed me off was the PowerPoint slide that was rolling that said: Forever.... throughout the whole service I was just hoping it said son forever and brother forever.... but it didn't. I was hoping pictures were included of his sisters and the few of his parents, cuz let's face it there are many pictures out there online and not one was included. We do not know the full issues surrounding this family but I was still hoping that those significant parts of Kobes life were documented, but they weren't.
Hopefully the death and grief brings vannessa and his sisters together and then hopefully that will create the path for the grandparents to enter vannessa and the children's lives.

May God bless them all. Dysfunction and toxicity within families is the worst thing ever.
